lion  number of employees  website wwwschwabcom the charles schwab corporation is a bank and brokerage firm based in san francisco california it was founded in  by charles r schwab it is on the list of largest banks in the united states and is one of the largest brokerage firms in the united states the company provides services for individuals and institutions that are investing online the company offers an electronic trading platform for the purchase and sale of financial securities including common stocks preferred stocks futures contracts exchangetraded funds options mutual funds and fixed income investments it also provides margin lending and cash management services the company also provides services through registered investment advisers contents  current operations  history  marketing  schwab charitable fund  see also  references  further reading  external links current operationsedit schwab operates in four main divisions investing wealth management banking and trading as of december   the company had  million active client brokerage accounts with  trillion in assets the company operated  branches in  states as well as a branch in each of puerto rico and london historyedit in  charles r schwab and two other partners launched investment indicator an investment newsletter at its height the newsletter had  subscribers each paying  a year to subscribe in april  the firm was incorporated in california as first commander corporation a wholly owned subsidiary of commander industries inc for traditional brokerage services and to publish the schwab investment newsletter in november of that year mr schwab and four others purchased all the stock from commander industries inc and in  mr schwab bought all the stock from what was once commander industries in  the company name changed to charles schwab  co inc in  the us securities and exchange commission allowed for negotiated commission rates and schwab set up a discount brokerage in september  schwab opened its first branch in sacramento ca and started offering discount brokerage services in  schwab began offering seminars to clients and by  schwab had  client accounts total doubling to  in  in  schwab established the industry’s first hour quotation service and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became a member of the nyse and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became the first to offer  order entry and quote service its first international office was opened in hong kong and the number of client accounts totaled  in  the company was purchased by bank of america for  million in  the company launched  noload mutual funds in  management including charles r schwab bought the company from bank of america for  million in  the company acquired mayer  scweitzer a market making firm allowing schwab to execute its customers orders without sending them to an exchange in  it was fined  for failing to arrange the best trades for its customers the unit was renamed schwab capital markets in  in  the company opened an office in london in  the company acquired the hampton company founded by walter w bettinger who became ceo of schwab in  in  schwab purchased us trust for  billion in  less than a year after the acquisition of us trust the us trust subsidiary was fined  million in a bank secrecy law case it was ordered to pay  million to the new york state banking department and  million to the federal reserve board on november   schwab announced an agreement to sell us trust to bank of america for  billion in cash the deal closed in the second quarter of  in november  schwab announced the  million acquisition of soundview technology group to add equity research capabilities david s pottruck who had spent the majority of his  years at the brokerage as charles r schwabs righthand man shared the ceo title with the companys founder from  to  in may  mr schwab stepped down and gave pottruck sole control as ceo on july   the companys board fired pottruck replacing him with its founder and namesake news of pottrucks removal came as the firm had announced that overall profit had dropped  percent to  million for the second quarter driven largely by a  percent decline in revenue from customer stock trading after coming back into control mr schwab conceded that the company had lost touch with our heritage and quickly refocused the business on providing financial advice to individual investors he also rolled back pottruck’s fee hikes the company rebounded and earnings began to turn around in  as did the stock the share price was up as high as  since pottruck’s removal ten times since the return of charles schwab the company’s net transfer assets or assets that come from other firms quadrupled from  to  schwab yieldplus fund this fund was named as one of the decades top ten fund disasters for the s “in written materials and in conversations with customers some schwab representatives omitted or provided incomplete or inaccurate material information relating to the funds characteristics risk and diversification and continued to represent yieldplus as a relatively lowrisk alternative to money market funds and other cash alternative investments that had minimal fluctuations in net asset value nav between sept   and feb   schwab sold over  billion in shares of yieldplus to customers which accounted for approximately  percent of the amount schwab customers invested in ultra shortterm bond funds during this time period schwabs solicited sales of yieldplus totaled approximately  billion approximately  percent of which were to customers  years of age or older schwab collected approximately  million in fees from sales of the fund”  from june  through june  the total return on schwab’s yieldplus fund yieldplus held large amounts of securities backed by illiquid longterm private label mortgages it also held long maturity corporate bonds and trust preferred securities in doing so schwab’s fund violated concentration and illiquidity limits stated in its prospectus and had much more credit and liquidity risk than it disclosed in its sec filings and marketing materials yieldplus’ long term securities including private label mortgage backed securities gave it a slight advantage over its peers prior to  unfortunately the extra yield was an order of magnitude smaller than the losses that followed when credit and liquidity spreads widened and the value of its long term holdings dropped significantly in  and  was  when other ultra short bond funds had little or no losses these large losses occurred because schwab’s yieldplus fund was not an ultra short bond fund as claimed by schwab it was instead an ultra long bond fund yieldplus’s heaviest reported losses occurred in early  yet schwab still appears to have understated these losses by significantly inflating the value of the fund’s holdings and therefore its navthe yieldplus fund made large risky investments in long maturity structured products such as subprime residential mortgage backed securities “rmbs” that were inconsistent with the sec’s definition of an ultra short bond fund schwab marketed the fund as a cash equivalent investment and as a safe alternative to money market funds with a higher yield and only slightly more risk such a claim would be incorrect for a typical conventionally managed ultra short bond fund but was especially false when made by schwab on behalf of the yieldplus fund in its marketing materials schwab compared returns on the yieldplus fund to returns on the lehman short us treasury  month index the treasury securities included in the lehman index have no credit risk are highly liquid and have short maturities the holdings of the yieldplus fund generally shared none of these attributes  yieldplus had  billion of investor losses including losses by the founder himself schwab closed the yieldplus funds in   in  the company acquired the k company on july   walter w bettinger the previous chief operating officer was named chief executive succeeding the companys namesake charles r schwab remained executive chairman of the company and said in a statement that he would continue to serve as a very active chairman bettinger stated chuck and i have worked closely together over the years preparing for this transition and we will continue to work closely together in our respective roles as executive chairman and ceo in  the company acquired optionsxpress in  the company acquired thomaspartners an asset management firm marketingedit in  havas worldwide then called euro rscg was chosen by charles schwab as its fullservice advertising agency in february  schwab announced that they had hired crispin porter  bogusky cpb as their lead creative agency with havas worldwide remaining to create ads for activetrader and optionsxpress in march  adweek reported on marketing material created by cpb for schwabs intelligent portfolio service starting in  the company launched a series of television ads featuring the slogan talk to chuck the tv ads were produced by havas worldwide then called euro rscg and directedanimated by bob sabistons flat black films talk to chuck ads appeared in print media online billboards and branch offices a wall street journal blog post described the ads as effective because they included a single memorable phrase in  the company launched an advertising campaign with the slogan own your tomorrow schwab charitable fundedit schwab charitable fund is a donor advised fund which preserves the anonymity of donors by not disclosing individual donor names professionallymanaged accounts are only available through independent investment advisors working with schwab advisor services a business segment of the charles schwab corporation it accepts contributions of real estate private equity or other noncash assets via a charitable intermediary with proceeds of your donation transferred to a donoradvised account upon liquidation this intermediary considers donations on a casebycase basis with a typical requirement that assets be valued at  or more see alsoedit comparison of online brokerages in the united states san francisco bay area portal companies portal referencesedit  a b schwab history retrieved    a b c d e f g the charles schwab corporation  form k annual report  a b c d e f g h i j k l schwab company history  fisher lawrence m february   bank america is selling schwab unit to founder new york times   company news charles schwab in an acquisition new york times june     schwab unit agrees to pay  fine bloomberg lp new york times october     schwab affiliate mayer  schweitzer to be renamed schwab capital markets lp press release pr newswire february     charles schwab acquired the hampton co a defined benefit and defined pi online november     mcgeehan patrick january   schwab to pay  billion for us trust new york times   brick michael july   us trust is fined  million in bank secrecylaw case new york times   bank of america to buy us trust forbes magazine november     schwab to acquire soundview technology group press release pr newswire november     schwab to buy soundview for  million bloomberg lp new york times november     charles schwab steps down as ceo of his brokerage los angeles times july    httpmoneyusnewscommoneyblogsfundobserverthedecadesworstfunddisasters  httpwwwfinraorgnewsroomfinraordersschwabpaymillioninvestorsimpropermarketingyieldplusbondfund  httpwwwslcgcompdfworkingpapersschwabyieldpluspdf  at schwab unkept promise to investors new york times  january    httpblogsfgatecompenderschwabshutteringbeleagueredyieldplusfunds  schwab announces acquisition of the k company press release pr newswire december     charles schwab steps down as ceo of his brokerage los angeles times july     schwab completes acquisition of optionsxpress press release business wire august     schwab announces agreement to acquire thomas partners press release business wire october     beltrone gabriel  charles schwab completes creative search crispin outstrips fallon for lead role adw