of that year mr schwab and four others purchased all the stock from commander industries inc and in  mr schwab bought all the stock from what was once commander industries in  the company name changed to charles schwab  co inc in  the us securities and exchange commission allowed for negotiated commission rates and schwab set up a discount brokerage in september  schwab opened its first branch in sacramento ca and started offering discount brokerage services in  schwab began offering seminars to clients and by  schwab had  client accounts total doubling to  in  in  schwab established the industry’s first hour quotation service and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became a member of the nyse and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became the first to offer  order entry and quote service its first international office was opened in hong kong and the number of client accounts totaled  in  the company was purchased by bank of america for  million in  the company launched  noload mutual funds in  management including charles r schwab bought the company from bank of america for  million in  the company acquired mayer  scweitzer a market making firm allowing schwab to execute its customers orders without sending them to an exchange in  it was fined  for failing to arrange the best trades for its customers the unit was renamed schwab capital markets in  in  the company opened an office in london in  the company acquired the hampton company founded by walter w bettinger who became ceo of schwab in  in  schwab purchased us trust for  billion in  less than a year after the acquisition of us trust the us trust subsidiary was fined  million in a bank secrecy law case it was ordered to pay  million to the new york state banking department and  million to the federal reserve board on november   schwab announced an agreement to sell us trust to bank of america for  billion in cash the deal closed in the second quarter of  in november  schwab announced t